WEEK 1 DELIVERABLE: KEY COLUMN NOTES FOR CRMLS SOLD DATA

1. Project Overview

The objective of this project is to develop a machine learning model that predicts the final sale price (ClosePrice) of residential single-family homes in California using historical CRMLS transaction data. The dataset contains property characteristics, geographic information, school district data, taxes, fees, amenities, and transaction details.
For this project, only records where PropertyType = Residential and PropertySubType = SingleFamilyResidence will be used. The project will follow a complete data science workflow including data exploration, preprocessing, feature engineering, model development, evaluation, and presentation.
The final goal is to identify the key factors that influence housing prices and build a model capable of accurately estimating property values.

